The paper deals with the multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) broadcast channel with delayed channel state information at transmitter (CSIT) and arbitrary antenna configurations. This topic falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) categories. The paper also involves designing achievable schemes and analyzing the achievable degrees-of-freedom (DoF) region, which falls under the signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM) categories. Additionally, the paper involves characterizing the achievable DoF region, which falls under the computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE) category.
